\b Variable Information - Employees Sheet\

\b0 This is where you fill in information about your employees\'92 availability and desired hours.
\b \

\b0 \

\b Name
\b0  - Name of employee \

\b Driver
\b0  - If the employee is a driver or can drive, insert TRUE, otherwise FALSE\

\b InShop
\b0  - Same thing as Driver but for InShop employees\

\b Days
\b0  - TRUE or FALSE on whether or not the employee works days\

\b Nights
\b0  - TRUE or FALSE on whether or not the employee works nights\

\b MaxHours
\b0  - The maximum amount of hours the employee can work\

\b TargetHoursDay
\b0  - The desired amount of day shift hours desired for an employee\

\b TargetHoursNight
\b0  - The desired amount of night shift hours desired for an employee\

\b TargetHoursInShop
\b0  - The desired amount of in-shop hours desired for an employee\

\b TargetHoursDriver 
\b0 - The desired amount of driving hours desired for an employee\

\b PriorityDriver
\b0  
\fs22 - 
\fs24 Gives priority of driver shift assignment to the employee with the lowest value. Each employee must have a number, 1, 2, 3, or 4, assigned.\

\b PriorityInShop
\b0  - Gives priority of driver shift assignment to the employee with the lowest value. Each employee must have a number, 1, 2, 3, or 4, assigned.\
\

\b WedAM->TuesPM 
\b0 - This is where specific shifts requested off are accounted for\'97insert TRUE if a shift has been requested off. Color code cells to ease the process if desired. Copy and paste color-coded cells to the corresponding sections of the schedule template to avoid color-coding more than once.\
\

\b Variable Information - Days/Nights Sheets\

\b0 This is where you will create shifts that need to be assigned.\
\

\b Shift 
\b0 - Descriptive but short name of the shift specifying its duration. Each shift name must be unique. Example set of shifts: 10-5, 11-R, 11-R(2)-indicating a shift that has one or more duplicates, 10-5(D)-indicating a driving shift\

\b Hours
\b0  - Number indicating the length in hours of the particular shift.\

\b Driver
\b0  - TRUE or FALSE indicating whether or not the shift is a driving shift (does not eliminate the necessity of a unique shift name)\
\

